Will do. I used stl since I can apply std::sort() and std::is_sorted().

We need a sorted list, since we scan linearly for call positions (see my comments in RegisterAllocator::GetCallerCalleePreference(()).

A better way would be to record the call positions on the linearised graph, in SsaLivenessAnalysis::NumberInstructions(). This way we do not need to sort the call positions array before using it.

Would that be acceptable?

